@startuml 05-split-brain-sequence
skinparam dpi 300
title Problem 5 — Split-Brain: BEAM vs. K8s Membership (TopScore)

box "Partition A" #f0f8ff
participant "pod-1\n(:global owner)" as P1
participant "pod-2" as P2
end box
box "Partition B" #fff0f0
participant "pod-3" as P3
participant "pod-4" as P4
end box
participant ":global" as G
participant "kubelet\n(all pods)" as K8s

note over P1,P4: healthy 4-node cluster\nsingle leaderboard singleton on pod-1

== AZ network blip — partition ==
P1 -x P3: connection lost
note over P1,P2: see pod-3,4 as nodedown
note over P3,P4: see pod-1,2 as nodedown
P3 -> G: re-register leaderboard (none visible)
note over P1,P4 #ffcccc: two singletons now accept\nscore increments independently

== K8s view throughout ==
K8s -> P1: liveness / readiness
P1 --> K8s: healthy
K8s -> P3: liveness / readiness
P3 --> K8s: healthy
note over K8s #ffcccc: K8s sees 4 healthy pods,\ntakes no action (blind to BEAM split)

== partition heals ==
P3 -> P1: reconnect
G -> G: name clash on leaderboard
G -> P3: kill duplicate singleton
note over P3 #ffcccc: scores accumulated in B discarded\nsilent data loss on heal
@enduml
